How much performance improvement does the SurePOS 350 offer over the previous
model?
A. 20%
B. 40%
C. 60%
D. 80%
Answer: C
Explanation: The new SurePOS 300 packs 60% more performance power.
What are two benefits of tool-free design?
A. It leads to higher up time.
B. It reduces IT service costs.
C. It allows more expandability options
D. It extends the useful life of the unit.
Answer: A,B
Explanation: Easy, virtually tool-free serviceability and
remote monitoring help keep POS maintenance costs low and
checkout lanes moving.
